sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OIDC as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OShift as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Upstream as Upstream App

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    AuthProxy->>OIDC: Redirect to authorization endpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Browser->>OIDC: Login with credentials<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OIDC->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>4180/TCP HTTP (Authorization code)
    AuthProxy->>OIDC: POST token endpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Client credentials + code
    OIDC-->>AuthProxy: Access token + ID token
    AuthProxy->>Redis: Store session (if redis mode)<br/>6379/TCP AES-GCM encrypted
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Set-Cookie + redirect
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /* (with session cookie)<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    AuthProxy->>AuthProxy: Validate session<br/>AES-CFB decrypt + HMAC verify
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS + injected headers<br/>X-Forwarded-User, X-Forwarded-Email

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: Kubernetes RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)
    Browser->>RBACProxy: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer token
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: TokenReview result (user identity)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: SubjectAccessReview result (allowed/denied)
    RBACProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>x-remote-user + x-remote-groups headers

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 3: OpenShift OAuth Sign-Out
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/sign_out<br/>4180/TCP HTTP<br/>Session cookie
    AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: DELETE /apis/oauth.openshift.io/v1/oauthaccesstokens/{token}<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer access token
    K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: 200 OK (token deleted)
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Clear cookie + redirect

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 4: Envoy ext_authz Integration (auth mode)
    Browser->>Envoy: GET /app-path<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    Envoy->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/auth<br/>4180/TCP HTTP<br/>Forwarded headers
    AuthProxy->>AuthProxy: Validate session/bearer
    AuthProxy-->>Envoy: 202 Accepted (authenticated)
    Envoy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>Authenticated headers
